}}'''Tunisia''' is a [[Nations|country]] that was added to [[BitLife: Life Simulator|BitLife]] in July 8, 2022.

On July 8, 2022, new countries were added to both iOS and Android. Along with Tunisia, there was also [[Andorra]], [[Angola]], [[Aruba]], [[Belize]], [[El Salvador]], [[Guatemala]], [[Guyana]], [[Haiti]], [[Nicaragua]], [[Papua New Guinea]], [[Paraguay]], [[Samoa]], and [[Uganda]]. This was added in a bug fix update prior to the upcoming Business Update.

==Information==
Tunisia, alongside Papua New Guinea, Venezuela, Belize, Iraq, Afghanistan, Nicaragua, El Salvador, Pakistan, Haiti, Syria, Guatemala, Angola, and Guyana are the 14 countries where a character can die suddenly, due to a terrorist attack, giving them the Unlucky ribbon. Family members can also die from these.

